Connection(I), Statement(I), PreparedStatement

Connection(I):
- connection is the session between java app and database

- Connection(I) is a factory of (Statement, PreparedStatement & DatabaseMetaData)
- i.e, object of Connection can be used to get the object of (Statement, PreparedStatement & DatabaseMetaData)

- the Connection (I) provides many methods like transection management like:
    - commit(), rollback(), setAutoCommit(), setTransectionalIsolation(), etc
    - also methods like createStatement(), close(), etc

Statement(I):
- use to create basic sql statement (accept sql string)
- provides methods to execute queries with database
- suitable for DDL queries like (create, alter & drop)

Statement(I) - extends - PreparedStatement(I) - extends - CallableStatement(I)

- different types of statement that JDBC follows:
    1. Create Statement (can create obj of this from connection interface)
        - int executeUpdate(DRL)
        - boolean execute(any SQL)
        - ResultSet executeQuery(DRL)
    2. Prepared Statement (connection.preparedStatement(SQL));
        - sub-interface of statement
        - used to execute parameterized queries
        - ps = conn.prepareStatement("insert into student values(?,?,?,?)");
          ps.setInt(1,45)
          ps.setString(2, "zaid")
        - after binding the appropriate placeholder, we need to call ps.executeUpdate(), ps.executeQuery(), etc

    3. Callable Statement



closing connection:
1) finally block - connection.close()
2) try with resources (from java 1.7 onwards) - best & modern way
   - syntax: try(connection){}catch(Exception e){}
   - no explicit close() required
